	  <p><in> Hi there! My name is Matthew Yohannes, I am currently a senior at Arapahoe High School and proud member of the Speech and Debate team. You see, speech and debate team or "forensics" is meant to promote public speaking and critical thinking skills in youth. <a href="https://www.speechanddebate.org/" target="_blank"> Here is the link to the NSDA website.</a><in/></p>
    <p><in> Forensics students compete in multiple events. The event that I compete in is called Extemporaneous Speaking. Typically, Extempers are given 30 minutes to write a speech that is 7 minutes in length about current events. Extemp is split into two different events, United States, and International. The latter involves current events and policy questions that occur domestically, and the former involves issues that occur across the globe. It's a very difficult, but highly awarding event. The purpose of this website is to provide resources for extempers, both novices and veterans, and help them grow as competitors.</p>
       <p> Here is a video of the 2016 National Champion in Domestic Extemp., Micah Cash, giving an extemp speech. This is a pretty good example of what extemperaneous speech would be like. Down below, you will find information on structuring a speech.</p>
